  "text": "As a group, there are more similarities than differences in the muscle pathology of the dystroglycanopathies. Variations relate to causal mutations and related amount of residual glycosylated a-dystroglycan. In FCMD the muscle biopsy shows active muscle fiber degeneration (necrosis of individual fibers) accompanied by muscle regeneration. Fiber size variability is present with numerous hypertrophic fibers. There is increased endomysial and perimysial connective tissue and fat that replaces lost muscle tissue. By immunohistochemistry the sarcolemma shows normal expression of b-dystroglycan accompanied by absent or reduced glycosylated a-dystroglycan ( Fig. 8) with preservation of core a-dystroglycan staining. In addition, the a-dystroglycan shows a shift in electrophoretic mobility [CITATION_1] .",
